 President Muhammadu Buhari has sacked two Executive Directors of the Nigerian Maritime Administration and Safety Agency (NIMASA) and appointed three new ones. The sack of Rotimi Fasakin (Executive Director Operations) and Gambo Ahmed (Executive Director, Maritime Labour and Cabotage Services) is coming on the heels of the appointment of Dr. Bashir Jamoh as new Director General of the agency. Sources hinted that a former Delta Speaker, Victor Ochei, will take over from Ahmed as the new Executive Director of Maritime Labour and Cabotage Services.  Details shortlyâ€¦